        {
            "title": "India's Hero MotoCorp to enter UK market with Hunk 440 motorcycle priced at 3,990 euros",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>(Reuters) -Hero MotoCorp, India's largest two-wheeler maker, said on Thursday it will enter the United Kingdom market with a partnership with Lancashire-based distributor MotoGB, making the company's products available in 51 countries.</p><p>\n              This comes on the heels of Hero's announcement earlier this month that it will sell its products in Italy and Spain.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n              Over the last few years, the company has partnered with distributors in Europe to expand its overseas shipments as rising costs and production disruptions hurt domestic sales.</p><p>\n              Through the partnership, Hero will sell its Euro 5+ compliant Hunk 440 motorcycle in the UK, priced at 3,990 euros (around $4,650), it said.</p><p>\n              The Hunk 440 will be sold through a network of more than 25 official sales and services outlets initially, expanding to more than 35 locations by 2026.</p><p>\n              ($1 = 0.8575 euros) </p><p>\n               (Reporting by Komal Salecha in Bengaluru; Editing by Janane Venkatraman)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/india-s-hero-motocorp-to-enter-uk-market-with-hunk-440-motorcycle-priced-at-3-990-euros-ce7d5dd8da8af027",
            "pub_date": "2025-10-23 20:15:40",
            "source": "marketscreener",
